Alert the User by a Pop-up:
    alert('Message!!')

Prompt to get a Input from the User:
    var answer = prompt('Question')

Print in Console:
    console.log('Message!!')

AND - &&
OR - ||
NOT - !

If-Else
    if(condition){
        expression
    }
    else if(condition) {
        expression
    }
    else(condition) {
        expression
    }

While Loop:
    while(condition) {
        expression
    }

For Loop:
    for(init; condition; step) {
        expression
    }

Check Index of a word or phase in a variable:
    variable.indexOf('word')

Defining a Function:
    function name(arguments) {
        expression
    }

Run a Function:
    name(arguments)

Repeating Function after every set interval:
    setInterval(funtionName, interval)              interval in ms 


ARRAY METHODS:
    push:
        array.push(value)
    pop:
        array.pop()
    unshift (adds to the front of the array):
        array.unshift(value)
    shift (removes from the front of the array):
        array.shift(value)
    indexOf:
        array.indexOf(element)
    slice (to make a copy of array):
        array.slice(start, end)
    forEach (to loop a function through all values of an array):
        array.forEach(function)
        array.forEach(function(el){
            console.log(el);
        })

OBJECT METHODS:
    Declaration:
        var name = {
            key: value,
            key: value
        }
    Accessing:
        name['key']
        name.key


DOM MANIPULATION:
    1. Selecting the Element:
        var h1 = document.querySelector('h1')

    2. Manipulating the Selected Element:
        h1.style.color = 'pink'

VIEW ALL PROPERTIES:
    console.dir(tag)

DOCUMENT METHODS:
    document.getElementById()
    document.getElementsByClassName()
    document.getElementsByTagName()

QUERY SELECTORS:
    document.querySelector()
    document.querySelectorAll()

MANIPULATING STYLES WITH CSS & JAVASCRIPT:
    Adding a Class in CSS:
        .newclass {
            color: blue;
            border: 10px solid blue;
        }

    Adding the New Class to the Selected Element:
        tag.classlist.add('newclass');
        tag.classlist.remove('newclass');
        tag.classlist.toggle('newclass');

MANIPULATING TEXT CONTENT:
    var tag = document.querySelector('p')
    tag.textContent                                 To retrieve the text content 
    tag.textContent = 'New Content'                 To alter the text content
    tag.innerHtml                                   To retrieve the RAW HTML used in the webpage

MANIPULATING ATTRIBUTES:
    tag.getAttribute(attributename)
    tag.setAttribute(attributename, replacementText)

EVENTS:
    Selecting an Element:
        button.addEventListener(type, function)
    
J-QUERY:
    Selecting elements:
        $('element')
    Changing Style of Elements:
        $('element').css('key','value')
    For multiple styles at once:
        $('element').css({
            key:'value',
            key:'value'
        })